value: John Flaxman, R.A. (d. 1826); Flaxman sale (remainder of his collection), Christie's, 11 April 1862, lot 450, bt. Mr Kibble; sold at Hodgson's, 25 January 1905, lot 372, bt. Quaritch; acquired from them by C.F. Murray, 1910

Sketchbook with marbled end boards and brown leather spine. Contains 31 leaves. The following pages have been removed: f.7, f.8, f.9, f.10, f.11, f.30, f.31, f.32, f.34, f.36, f.41 and f.44. The following pages have been removed and mounted separately: f.37, f.39 and f.45.
Mr Kibble / John Flaxman's Sketches / purchased at the Sale / at Messrs Christie Manson & Woods / April 1862 (in another hand)
